article_title: Air Travel Resumes After Indonesian Volcano Eruption
article_text:
JAKARTA, Indonesia—Air travel was largely back to normal on Sunday after ash from a massive eruption on Indonesia's main island closed airports and grounded hundreds of flights across the region late last week.

Authorities have reopened most of the seven airports that were closed on the island of Java following the eruption of Mount Kelud late Thursday, including the two largest—in Surabaya, Indonesia's second-largest city, and in...
